gov.va.med.srcalc.util

Class SearchResults<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.med.srcalc.util.SearchResults<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of objects found

    public final class SearchResults<T>
extends java.lang.Object

    Encapsulates the results of a search, including the actual items found and whether the list of items was truncated due to a maximum. Immutable.

    Per Effective Java Item 17, this class is marked final because it was not designed for inheritance.

      • fromList

        public static <T> SearchResults<T> fromList(java.util.List<T> foundItems,
                            int max)
        Constructs an instance by truncating the given list to the given maximum. We provide this method because it is common for search code to detect exceeding a maximum by searching for max + 1 results and then truncating the list.
        Returns:
        a SearchResults containing the first max items in foundItems
